<Date>1589595607569<//Date><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
I decided to look into buying a new mattress. I narrowed down my options and decided to purchase a nectar. I also really wanted a adjistable base. I called and spoke with a gentleman named Eduardo. Now at first I was only going to buy the base and buy the mattress from the actual nectar website. But Eduardo informed me that I could buy it from mattress firm and the adjustable base would come free! Well I was sold. He took his time going over all my questions and explaining everything. I told him I also needed someone to come setup the base because I'm not proficient in such and honestly don't want to be bothered. He assured me that he could send someone out to do it for me and they would wear face masks,booties and the whole kaboodle. I waited to receive a email from the nectar site or fed ex but I never did. I received a email from Macy's that my new sheet sets had arrived. When I went down to the package room lo and behold my mattress was sitting there. After managing to get it onto the elevator, I walked in my front door and my cell phone was ringing. It was Eduardo calling to tell me my mattress had just been delivered. I was so amazed that even though I never received any email he had stayed on top of it and made sure that I knew it was there. I'm sure he sells lots  of mattresses but this type of personal attention is pretty much non existent these days. As someone who also works in customer service I can tell you he is top of the line!</review>

<username>Lana Dancy</username><Time>1628866367362</Time><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
Noel Flynn is a devoted artist in the true sense of the word. He went above-and-beyond to help me find a frame that would best match two beautiful frames I purchased over 20 years ago. Unbeknownst to me, until we talked further, Noel was the one who helped me pick those frames out when he was working for another frame shop back then. For such a small shop, his frame selection is immense, and I doubt you will find a larger selection nearby. It is well worth your time to find his shop in downtown Old Roseville. He intently listened to what I wanted for the matting, also. I absolutely love the result! As an aside, he is displaying other artists‚Äô work (and his) in his shop. I absolutely love the beautiful woodworking, secret-compartment boxes there. Go there! You won‚Äôt be disappointed.</Text>

<GmapID>0x809b2038f7bee817:0xb626113861cfe3b6</GmapID><user_name>Kim Carty<//user_name>< review>
I definitely recommend Noel Flynn Gallery and Frame Factory as the best framing services available!  Regardless of age or location, we all search for those people who are trustworthy; and if we are lucky, a lasting bond forms. It has always been very evident that Noel Flynn loves his work.  He is professional, knowledgeable, and caring.  He has a talent for recognizing exact shades of color, complimentary textures, and quality materials.  He manages to pull these elements together for an overall excellent combination. He accomplishes this while working with his customers.
At the start of each new endeavor, Noel asks what it is that I want.  Sometimes I have a vague idea.  Sometimes, I am overwhelmed and have no idea at all.  He patiently guides me through the process of finding that -‚ÄúYes, that‚Äôs it ‚Äì the perfect fit‚Äù.
Getting a picture framed can be an extremely stressful situation for me.  I have a difficult time making choices, hoping not to make a costly mistake!  Many years ago, I did not listen to Noel‚Äôs advice about how the exact colors of the same frame may not necessarily be the same, if they are ordered after a significant amount of time has passed.  I had fallen in love with a specific frame that I wanted to match a previously purchased one.  Unfortunately, the new frame did not match the original.  In fact, they made each other look terrible together!  I knew I had made a hopeless mistake that I had to just accept. Unfortunately, this meant putting this latest purchase in a cupboard out of sight where it stayed for quite awhile.
I am now retired, and have time to return to my goal of properly framing my artwork with the best quality frames.  I recently shared my ‚Äúdisaster frame story‚Äù with Noel.  He was extremely generous in offering me an equivalent replacement.  I was overwhelmed by his generosity! I do not believe that there are many businesses that would even consider making such an offer!
Finally, I want to mention that Noel offers custom etched picture mats. These beautiful, unique creations add a very distinct detail without being too busy.  I have used them on my black and white family portraits and definitely plan to buy more. Now, 30 years later, I realize I was lucky enough to find my perfect frames, and that enduring bond I was looking for.  I found all of this at Noel Flynn Gallery and Frame Factory.<//review>

loren loren</username>
< text>
Started working with Noel about 3 years ago. I'm a very particular customer...Attention to detail. And I make that known. Our initial conversation resulted in connection. It's a good feeling when you finally find what you've been looking for. Since then, Noel has produced some fantastic custom frames for my match cover categories. Normally 10 to 12 per frame, mat cut to accommodate them individually.
Then we got into float frames (usually 11x14 to 20x24). Glass on both sides (so you can see the back) with a clear plastic custom sheet in between to keep the covers from moving. Plastic sheet needed to have openings cut to receive those particular match covers and result in a symmetrical layout. And if that is not enough to deal with, If you screw up on the first through the last opening....Throw it away...No fixing it. We started on the first few and they turned out GREAT in all aspects.
I have many different categories....We kept going. Noel has completed 176!   All will be shown in Roseville's Blue Line Art Gallery, April 16th to 30th, 2021.
Noel has been absolutely wonderful to work with over the years. Nice guy, knows what he's doing, stands behind his work and he has been doing this for a long time. What more could you ask for?
Very happy to give him 5 stars.    Loren Moore< /text>

< Text>
Quite a number of years ago, I needed a rush (two days) framing job in order to properly display a large photograph at a funeral.  Mr. Flynn was then at his previous location off Douglas and was very busy (nothing has changed in that regard).  Yet he was the ONE framer in Roseville who would even consider taking on the job.  After significant inconvenience beyond his normal work hours, he had it beautifully done - and ahead of schedule.  Fortunately, I have not had another rush job, but since that experience, all my framing work, which is significant due to a special interest, has gone only to Mr. Flynn, and I have never been even a little bit disappointed.

While every aspect of his framing is very well done, his sense of spacing and attention to perfection in doing the matting work is, in my opinion, nothing short of superb - I have not seen better anywhere.  And whenever I have been unsure of how to have a frame job accomplished, I have never regretted going with what he thinks.

While some might feel the cost a bit "pricey," it is easy to respond that "You get what you pay for."  But that is often not true - you pay for high quality, but you don't get it.  With Noel Flynn's Gallery and Frame Factory, you do get what you pay for!< /Text>

<user>118232576103894669524<//user><review>I remember the 1st time I ate @ a food truck in East Oakland. It was tacos and there were not that many "food trucks" around.  These days there are food trucks that sell everything!  Even Indian food!

Dum is a great food truck that also has a brick and mortar restaurant called Ritu.  Great reasonable prices and small selection of goodies or snacks.  The rotis are my favorite- warm, doughy and chewy with spices.  Wash it down with a sweet mango lassi!   There are 2 staff members that work inside the truck.  Both wearing masks and there are hand sanitizers available. Follow them on social media to find out where the truck will be next!< /review></record>

<Time>1613513929589< /Time><Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
We love this place!¬†The food here is fabulous. It's always¬†fresh and full of flavor, the atmosphere is casual (and safe during COVID) and the service is exemplary.

Some of our favorites.....the Kale Chaat are just the way we like them - a crisp flaky crust, not doughy or greasy.¬†The Artichoke Pakoras are also light, crispy and delicious. Their Veg Biryani, Jalfrezi and Malai Kofta dishes are savory and delightful.¬†The menu is excellent and they vary it which¬†is something that we really enjoy -¬†trying new dishes each time we order from them.

Also, as vegans that avoid gluten, the chefs are brilliant about putting together a superb menu for us. Because of our restrictions we often feel like we're relegated to a single item on the menu when we order out but this is never the case at Ritu. We always have choices.¬†It's also *super* reassuring to know that we can trust them with our food restrictions.

The prices are fair for the¬†quality of fare and the portions are generous.<//Text>

< review>
I really love the ambiance of the restaurant. The decor feels very warm and inviting. The lighting makes me feel that we were in Christmas time.

I love the Dahi Puri, the crispy and tangy combo was really delicious. The crispy kale chaat was also very creative and delicious, basically cleaned the bowl by myself. Another favorite is the veggie korma, which is surprising to me since I love meat. But the curry sauce of the korma was very tasty, I cleaned this bowl again (notice a pattern here?).

The desserts were also amazing! I had a low expectation because the owner said they're not dessert chefs. However, they're really tasty and unique. I'd definitely come back for the pistachio pot de creme.

The Almanac beer that accompanied the meal was delicious too, such a good addition to the already delicious meal.< /review>

<pictures>None<//pictures><text>It's going to be one of my go to places for comfort food.

1. I like the fact that I don't have to compromise on my health or hygiene to eat a good Indian meal in this place. Everything was delicious, hygenic ( at least looked hygenic ), but not loaded with cream or soaked in oil.

2. Multiple Vegetarian and Vegan options. Roasted cauliflower seemed like a hit ( although I did not try it ).

3. My favourite was the 3 Chaat sampler for $15. I thought this was extremely reasonable and offered delicious options to try out multiple dishes without filling yourself up with any one. I clubbed the dahi Puri ( highly recommended ), sprouts and beet chaat. Everything was delicious.

4. We also ordered the chicken. It was delicious, however for those of you looking for authentic butter chicken, this was not the same. It was cooked in pumpkin gravy. I liked it anyway.

The service was good and we had no wait time for a meal on Saturday night. I recommend trying it out.<//text>< user_id>

<Time>1485626417038</Time><Rating>5<//Rating><text>The food is hands down one of the best tasting Indian food I've had in Bay Area.

Lot of Indian restaurants in Bay Area are scared of using spices because of the audience, but dum achieves this nice balance where anyone can enjoy the true Indian soul food.

The flavors were amazing!! And as an Indian I've had these items in India, what dum served did hit the spots.

We went during sf restaurant week but ordered al a carte, as we wanted to try as many items as we can between the 4 of us. There was a strong consensus among us that food was no doubt delicious, and we all agreed on the balance of favors, just well done.

The place is trendy and service is always with a smile. Chef does take his time, but that little wait is well worth it. It's more of experience rather than simple chow down session.

If you've been let down by tons of typical Indian restaurants in the Bay Area, then do try Dum. They also have truck in the city</text><pics>None<//pics>< Response>

< user_id>
106808048360804793220</user_id>
<user_name>Marc Geredes</user_name><Date>1366414089767<//Date><rate>5</rate>< Text>
I do most of the work on our cars, and my daughter's 2003 BMW 325i is no exception.  For example, I recently replaced the rear differential and one of the motor mounts.  On occasion, I've taken the 325i down to Stevens Creek BMW to give me a diagnostic when I'm having trouble diagnosing the problem.  I try to never have them do any work though, because if you know anything about cars, it would become crystal clear that they charge well beyond what they should for the repairs they make (and they make repairs they shouldn't).

Anyway, my daughter brought the BMW home recently and it was overheating.  I was able to determine that the water pump had failed (the impeller had actually disintegrated).  I replaced the water pump, expansion tank, transmission thermostat, and flushed the entire cooling system to make sure I got all the impeller fragments out.  After filling the cooling system, I found that for some reason, I couldn't bleed all the air out of the system after many attempts to do so.  I feared that possibly my daughter had driven the car too long when the car had overheated and that she may have warped the cylinder head.

A friend had recently told me about William, saying he was the most honest BMW repair person you could hope to find, so I decided to give him a try.  Not only did he diagnose the problem (a cracked radiator, which I was unable to diagnose) he and the team at Bay Area Motor Works fixed it at a cost, and I probably shouldn't say this, probably lower than they should have.

Needless to say, I'm a huge fan!  While I'll continue to do as much of the repair work as possible on our cars, I'll be calling William and the team of experts at Bay Area Motor Works if I need help on our BMW.  I can honestly say he and his team are the most honest you'll find in the Bay Area...and I should know!< /Text>

Visiting a dentist is anxiety inducing already, and it is upsetting that there are dentists out there like this that are more interested in getting more money than being honest with their patients. I definitely wouldn‚Äôt recommend going here.< /Review>

Dining Al Fresco use to sound exotic but is now the New Norm. That being said, Round Tables Al Fresco was enjoyable and the centrally located fire pit was a nice touch on a sunny but chilly February afternoon. Lunch Specials B+. < review>
Ok... This isn't you typical Round Table... It's Round Table Clubhouse!.. ok.. üëç other than the awesome pizzas,  I've tried out their garlic cheese toast, nice n crispy. Garden salad, wings were awesome. They fry them rather than bake them in the oven. You can go both ways, I prefer the fried. Sliders we're good. I'm not a fan of sliders, because usually most other restaurants sliders r boring and tasteless.. so I gave it a shot and ordered some and was pretty impressed. They are like tiny burgers with a taste. They also have a bar. Ordered michelada which was also spicy and loaded with flavor. Pretty cool atmosphere with games for the kids. Cool spot to watch any game that's on. Great for dates too. We'll have fun! üçïüçîüçó< /review>
